 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 9:40:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=35>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What are you doing to kill the maurader he just womps on</span><hr size=1> Stay away from the marauder if you can.  I rarely find him up.  Our massive druid population (on Tunare, who'd a thunk it) keeps him dead.<br>
<br>
But if you do aggro him, use the &quot;/pet back off || /pet attack&quot; hot key (a must have) so that the pet gets whomped on instead of you, then chain heal using refresh and renew.  Don't chain pets, or you will die.<br>
<br>
Also, use the fire pet, so that the two goblins that aren't getting beat on will still take significant damage from his higher DS.  Make sure that the pet kills the marauder first. <p><div align="center"> <a href="#"><img src="http://www.nemeandesign.net/eq/sig2.jpg" width="382" height="66" border="0" onClick="window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=528641', 'morillion', 'WIDTH=800,HEIGHT=600')"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lancetheavatar>Lancetheavatar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lonedragon02/soul.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 6:20:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What are you doing to kill the maurader he just womps on</span><hr size=1> I tried the BloodGills a few nights ago, becoming so sickened with Echo (from 20 to at least 40 on three characters does that to people). I can say that while I held the camp, it was the best I had seen for a long, long time.<br>
<br>
Here is what I did. I am a level 46 Magician by the way, with only 180 int at the moment, so it should not be too hard for anyone with more int or even KEI. By the way, I did not have KEI or clarity. Note: I have all the focus items as well, which likely helped out.<br>
<br>
The basic outline as the first post of this actually works, but I twinked it a little:<br>
<br>
On the uper level of the camp, each corner has two BloodGills.  Anyways, Summon a focused Fire pet and send him in. Nuke each goblin with your level 1 or 4 nuke(Yes, that is right, with your level 1 or 4 nuke) and then sit back and heal your pet with Renew( I think it is renew) summoning. Works like a charm. The pet and the innate fire shield tears through them. One will go down, and shortly after the other one will start to run. You can either nuke its last life, which was about a buble or so of health, or simply let the pet chase after it. Go to the next spawn site, wash, rinse, repeat. <br>
<br>
Unlike most, I did not return topside to med, I simply meditated in the water if I needed to, which was very seldom. I only had the camp for maybe 30 minutes, maybe a little longer(but not much) and went from 40% into 46 to near 60%. 1% a kill is definetly not bad experience, and as I believe was said before in an earlier post, that means 100 kills = 1 happy Magician shouting ding. <br>
<br>
Anyways, I hope this helps. <br>
<br>
If you are ever down in Vazaelle, look me up, would be great to meet you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amelie@themagicianstower>Amelie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(3/2/03 12:42:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Map !</span><hr size=1> Here is my 2 cents on this very nice camp, the map :<br>
